titleInfo.title: USA v. Cisneros et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER regarding 27 Motion to Modify Conditions of Release as to John S. Cisneros (1). Upon consideration of the defendant's motion to amend conditions of release, filing no. 27, IT IS ORDERED: The motion for modification of conditions of release is denied subject to the following. The motion may be renewed at such as Priscilla Huff: 1. (a) has been admitted to participate in drug court or (b) has begun an intensive treatment program, and 2. can document that she has tested clear of drugs for three consecutive weeks. Ordered by Magistrate Judge David L. Piester. (LKH)

titleInfo.title: USA v. Cisneros et al
titleInfo.subTitle: PRELIMINARY ORDER OF FORFEITURE sustaining 62 Motion as to John S. Cisneros (1) and Brandi L. Phillips (2). Based upon Count II of the Indictment and the Defendants' pleas of guilty, the United States is hereby authorized to seize the $579.00 in United States currency. The Defendants interest in said property is hereby forfeited to the United States for disposition in accordance with the law. Upon adjudication of all third-party interests, this Court will enter a Final Order of Forfeiture pursuant to 21 U.S.C., ยง 853(n), in which all interests will be addressed. titleInfo.title: USA v. Cisneros et al
titleInfo.subTitle: FINAL ORDER OF FORFEITURE regarding 77 Motion for Final Forfeiture as to defendants John S. Cisneros (1), and Brandi L. Phillips (2). The Plaintiff's Motion for Final Order of Forfeiture is sustained. All right, title and interest in and to the $579.00 in United States currency, held by any person or entity, is hereby forever barred and foreclosed. The same hereby is, forfeited to the United States of America. The United States Marshal for the District of Nebraska is directed to dispose of said property in accordance with law. Ordered by Senior Judge Warren K. Urbom. (1 Certified copy to USM)(LKH)FINAL ORDER OF FORFEITURE regarding 77 Motion for Final Forfeiture as to defendants John S. Cisneros (1), and Brandi L. titleInfo.title: USA v. Cisneros et al
titleInfo.subTitle: JUDGMENT as to defendant John S. Cisneros (1). DEFENDANT pleaded guilty to counts I and II of the Indictment and is committed to the custody of the Bureau of Prisons for 121 months; 5 years supervised release with special conditions; $100.00 special assessment. Final order of forfeiture filed on 06/22/2009 as to Count II. The defendant shall forfeit the defendants interest in the following property to the United States: $579.00 in United States currency. Ordered by Senior Judge Warren K. Urbom. (4 Certified copies to USM)(LKH, )
